column5: well i had to get a few fillets for tomorrow night for a friend coming to fish with me... im thinking no biggy... ill go out tonight and get a few eyes for supper tomorrow...  sure enough... wind was 30+km gusting 40+km... yaaaaay...lol  so i limped out to a sheltered little honey hole... and sure enough i popped 6 in an hour...all but one were over 3 pounds... man fish love wind... so 2 went in the well and i headed home...  was i ever glad i know some sheltered areas to fish...    mike
I'll bring the napkins !!!!!Thats enough for me, what are you gonna eat Bud
i think 2 3 pounders will feed us both...
oh nay nay................3lbs of walleye,is a promisary note that food will follow
You've been watching too much Pinette.
Wind and walleye = match made in heaven.     He is a funny man.
Mike , should i be bring'n my Jimmy Flyn out fit so's i don't get wet ...........
